brewery.brewery_description:
Old Bust Head Brewing Company is named for a bygone crossroads in the rolling hills of Fauquier County, Virginia.  The locals who dubbed the corner ‘Bust Head’ enjoyed not only the potent libations brewed there, but also a little good humor. 

While we're serious about the art of crafting exceptional beer, and about our passion for our community and our environment, we salute those past and present who keep things playfully in perspective and make life a bit more enjoyable for all of us.

beer.beer_name: Old Jail Pumpkin Peach Brown Ale

beer.beer_description: Our deep amber Vixen Irish Red, has a luster as rich as the thick-coated red fox that roams the local wood. Medium bodied, with a clean finish, Vixen draws you in with a sweet carmel allure up front and gives chase with hints of roasted malt through the taste. A tea-like soft bitterness on the backend is so pleasing, you just may find you’re reaching for another glass of this wily brew.

beer.beer_description: Brewed in the tradition of an English Pale Ale, but infused with the spirit of new American craft brews, our flagship beer is drinkable, balanced, and enjoyable year- round. Additions of Goldings, Fuggle, and Cascade hops provide our pale ale with the aromas of floral hop tones and subdued fruitiness, as well as imparting a refreshing, clean bitterness. Our use of caramel malt in the grain bill balanc- es out our generous hop additions, and provides the beer with a smooth and bready backbone. Perfectly balanced and sessionable, it’s our brewmaster’s favorite beer!

beer.beer_description: From Civil War scrawls on the walls of Graffiti House to illicit aerosol artistry we all endeavor to leave our mark.  Our Graffiti House West Coast Style IPA asserts its presence with a potent aroma of passion fruit, mango, guava, and citrus.  The bold and juicy tropical body is a unique signature of the Mosaic hops, while Cascade hops contribute to a clean citrus finish for a flavor so singular it leaves its own indelible impression.

beer.beer_description:
As the colors come out each fall it is not just the
turning of the leaves we celebrate but the limited
release of our annual Oktoberfest. With a malty,
yet clean build and full caramel tones, our
Oktoberfest Märzen lager perfectly balances a
toasty, bready sweetness with a touch of hops.

Francis Fauquier, namesake of our home county, was no stranger to gambling.  In fact, it was over a game of poker, complete with some rousing table talk, that Francis lost his family inheritance, but gained himself a spot as the governor of Virginia.  In keeping with Fauquier’s spirit, we took a gamble with our Belgian Style Wit, adding passionfruit and guava purée for a new take on this traditional style.  Packed with flavor, but still sessionable enough to enjoy again and again, we recommend enjoying Table Talk with some lively company.

items.checkin_comment: It is hard to believe a beer could be malty and hoppy at the same time but this one is.  Reminds me of a brown ale

From Civil War scrawls on the walls of Graffiti House to illicit aerosol artistry we all endeavor to leave our mark.  Our Graffiti House West Coast Style IPA asserts its presence with a potent aroma of passion fruit, mango, guava, and citrus.  The bold and juicy tropical body is a unique signature of the Mosaic hops, while Cascade hops contribute to a clean citrus finish for a flavor so singular it leaves its own indelible impression.

Brewed in the tradition of an English Pale Ale, but infused with the spirit of new American craft brews, our flagship beer is drinkable, balanced, and enjoyable year- round. Additions of Goldings, Fuggle, and Cascade hops provide our pale ale with the aromas of floral hop tones and subdued fruitiness, as well as imparting a refreshing, clean bitterness. Our use of caramel malt in the grain bill balanc- es out our generous hop additions, and provides the beer with a smooth and bready backbone. Perfectly balanced and sessionable, it’s our brewmaster’s favorite beer!

Breaking away from the recent trend of super-hopped India Pale Ales, Wildcat is brewed to provide the aroma and taste hop-heads crave, without overwhelming your pallet. Brewed with four different hops, and five different malts, our India Pale Ale is complex, while still remaining approachable. Magnum, Cascade, Liberty, and Saaz hops lend our India Pale Ale a citrus aroma, with a touch of noble hop distinction and herbal complexity, and a smooth, clean bitterness. The use of five different malts in our grain bill provide Wildcat with the complex flavors of malty sweetness, bread, and caramel that we use to round out our brew. Just like the ‘Free State’ community that inspired its name, Wildcat India Pale Ale blazes its own path into history.

Our deep amber Vixen Irish Red, has a luster as rich as the thick-coated red fox that roams the local wood. Medium bodied, with a clean finish, Vixen draws you in with a sweet carmel allure up front and gives chase with hints of roasted malt through the taste. A tea-like soft bitterness on the backend is so pleasing, you just may find you’re reaching for another glass of this wily brew.

Brewed in the style of traditional Czech Pilsners, Chukker is a crisp, easy- drinking offering. Unlike most Czech Pilsners, we actually bitter Chukker with a high-alpha German hop, in order to cut down on the classic notes of freshly cut grass. While this deviates slightly from the expected pilsner taste, it makes Chukker a bit more drinkable, and adds a pleasant, slightly minty bitterness on the backend. Saaz hops do contribute some grassy notes, along with spice, that balances out the taste of toasted bread from the malts, giving this brew a velvety soft mouthfeel.

Named for the golden chalice bestowed on the winner of the Virginia Gold Cup races—an antique cup first granted to horse and rider by Catherine the Great—our Russian Imperial Stout with its black, velvety, opulence is as rich and complex as the Czarina who was a fan of the dark brew. A dark-berry sweetness underlies roasted tones of bittersweet chocolate and espresso coating the mouth with a smooth, lingering, fullness worthy of the cup!

Using our Oatmeal Stout as a base, and locally roasted coffee from Monument Coffee Roasters, our Caramel Macchiato Stout has the rich aroma a flavored iced coffee. Vanilla extract, and natural sugar combine with the roasted malts to lend a subtle caramel sweetness for a brew that is refreshing in the summer and decadent in the winter!

Rich and full bodied, our Chinquapin Chestnut Porter is sure to please fans of more robust beer styles. Every batch of Chinquapin Chestnut Porter is made with molasses and a heaping portion of real chestnuts brewed with a blend of dark malts for a roasted richness with hints cocoa and coffee. As a thank you to the tree that makes the smooth, nutty taste of our porter possible, a portion of the proceeds from Chinquapin Chestnut Porter are donated to The American Chestnut Foundation.

beer.beer_name: Old Jail Pumpkin Peach Brown Ale
beer.beer_description: Like the ghost that is said to dwell in the Old Jail in nearby Warrenton, Virginia, a pumpkin and peach essence haunts, but does not overpower, our Old Jail Pumpkin Peach Brown Ale. An aroma of sweet spice and pumpkin pie precedes the body of caramel nuttiness with hints of molasses, roasted brown sugar, and vanilla. A dissipating smokiness from the Cherrywood Smoked Malt finishes the taste imparting a fresh baked flavor to this unearthly Brown Ale.

Named for the rural Fauquier village where hundreds of ducks return each year to make their summer homes, our Sumerduck Saison brings a flavor of Spring with fruity Belgian esters, a subtle tartness, and delicate earthy notes. A touch of rye adds a peppery spice, and wheat malt a silky mouth feel to this easy drinking Farmhouse Ale.

2+ lbs per barrel of Galaxy and Mosaic hops, and a heavy tropical aroma of pineapple and mango, with a hint of peach. Smooth flavor. Clean finish with a bit of bitter at the end. Great overall summer beer.

Amarillo® and Simcoe® hops dominate
the field in our bold American Pale Ale.
Like the Shorthorn cattle bred and improved
by our American pioneers, Shorthorn APA
raises the bar with bright citrus, juicy tropical
fruit, and clean pine aromas from American
grown hops — a proud addition to an
American pedigree!!

Like the two time Gold Cup steeple chase winner that gave our ultra-aromatic double IPA its name, Sonic Charm starts with a burst of flavor right out of the gates.  A tropical juice bomb of passion fruit, guava and pineapple is tempered by the bright flavors of sweet grapefruit, orange peel, and citrus.  With little bitterness, and 8.3 alcohol by volume, you’ll have to watch this one as you'll reach the finish line in record time.

Citra and Hallertau Blanc shine brightly in our intentionally hazy Double IPA! Certain Swagger blazes a new trail in our Double IPA line, with a soft and pillowy mouthfeel, and the looks to match. A heavy dry-hop of Citra and Hallertau Blanc hops lend Sauvignon Blanc and white grapefruit aromas, and the unmistakable flavors of fresh mango juice and passion fruit. And just to make sure you can taste every pound of hops in this ultra-fresh brew, we left this one completely unfiltered!

With the unmistakable flavor of fresh squeezed pink lemonade, you’ll want nothing else to quench your summer thirst! Aged on strawberries and raspberries, our kettle soured wheat ale balances sweet and tart perfectly, just like your favorite summertime treat. A hint of pink Himalayan salt keeps the Pink Lemonade shockingly drinkable, while also making sure it stays true to it's name.

A showcase of hops without the high ABV associated with most IPAs, Quickfix is a great offering for people that want a beer that has full hop flavor and aroma, but that they can enjoy for multiple rounds. Amarillo and Simcoe hops work seamlessly together to give Quickfix a potent aroma of orange peel, citrus, and floral hoppiness. On your first sip, you’ll be greeted by the flavors of orange and grapefruit, which give way to light notes of apricot and peach, and are washed away by a slight piney bitterness and supporting malt. Bright, light, but still full of flavor, Quickfix is a great “all-day” sipper.

Hidden behind the dark exterior of our Covert h’Ops Black IPA are layers on layers of complex hops. A strong bitterness of pine and grapefruit from kettle additions of CTZ, Northern Brewer, and Cascade hops compliments flavors of dark chocolate and roasted espresso from the malts, while a generous dry-hopping of Mosaic and Cascade hops lends an unexpected tropical and floral hop aroma. Covert h’Ops Black IPA is a perfect tribute to the secret intelligence operators who used to occupy our brewery buildings!
Limes, oranges and salt collide in our tart and funky Gose base for a new take on a beach-side classic.

Generously hopped with Citra, Chinook, Centennial, CTZ, and Cascade. Aggressively dry-hopped on more Citra and Centennial. 10.1% ABV. 100 IBU. Juicy, tropical, citrusy, dank, resiny, floral, and complex. Ya'll wanted an imperial, so we're giving you one.

The sweet aroma of honey and oats set the palate for the honey, oat, and milk chocolate flavors and subdued roasted tones that carry through to a light coffee finish.

We’ve accentuated the tropical notes arising from the mosaic hops in our Graffiti House  IPA by aging this popular favorite on mango puree.  A pronounced mango aroma and increased sweet tropical tone step up the exotic in this West Coast Style IPA!

Just on the nose alone, there’s no missing Coconut Gold Cup! Aged on both toasted and cream of coconut, this variant has the unmistakable sweet aroma of a freshly opened fruit from this tropical tree. A flavor of shredded coconut follows, perfectly balancing our deep and rich brew. One sip will take your tastebuds on a ride—close your eyes, and you just might think you’re biting into a classic Mounds Bar.
